                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/805: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-13T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 13, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. Your 117, September 5, 1 p.m. We are going forward with our trade agreement
                    preparations on the assumption that conditions arising from the war will not be
                    such as to preclude the possibility of the conclusion of a mutually satisfactory
                    agreement.</p>
                <p>The war has not altered our ability to offer to Belgium increased facilities for
                    Belgian imports into the United States. We here do not now know in what measure
                    the war will affect our export trade with Belgium. We are assuming however that
                    the Belgian Government will continue to be in a position to offer American trade
                    adequate compensation for the concessions we will be prepared to make.</p>
                <p>In view of the existing situation in Europe we feel that definite decision
                    regarding the place where the definitive negotiations are to be held should be
                    deferred until early October.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
